      "name": "Hemolysis model adequacy assessment via published literature survey",
      "description": "A structured review of published CFD hemolysis studies for centrifugal blood pumps was conducted to assess model form adequacy. Seventeen peer-reviewed publications were screened; twelve reported relative hemolysis index predictions consistent with the power-law damage accumulation model used here. The literature survey supports the conclusion that the selected model form is adequate for the CPB COU and that the RH < 1 acceptance criterion is clinically defensible.",
